  "summary": "TPC-H is OLAP-heavy with Q1/Q6 as embarrassingly parallel full-table scans (lineitem ~100M+ rows) on an HDD. Q3 is the bottleneck: 3-way join with high intermediate cardinality requires careful join ordering and partition-based parallelism to avoid memory/I/O explosion. Dominant patterns: date range filters on lineitem (high selectivity), low-cardinality hash aggregation in Q1 (4 groups), and multi-way joins in Q3. Key levers: (1) morsel-driven parallelism across 64 cores for Q1/Q6 scans, (2) columnar storage + compression to minimize HDD I/O, (3) hash join with radix partitioning to fit working set in L3 cache (44MB), (4) bloom filters for semi-join reduction in Q3."
